def calculate_growth_rates(data):
    """Calculate year-over-year growth rates for each column"""
    growth_rates = pd.DataFrame(index=data.index[1:], columns=data.columns)
    
    for col in data.columns:
        for i in range(1, len(data)):
            current_val = data.iloc[i][col]
            previous_val = data.iloc[i-1][col]
            
            # Only calculate if both values are non-null
            if pd.notna(current_val) and pd.notna(previous_val) and previous_val != 0:
                growth_rate = ((current_val - previous_val) / previous_val) * 100
                growth_rates.iloc[i-1][col] = growth_rate
            else:
                growth_rates.iloc[i-1][col] = np.nan
    
    return growth_rates

{"code": "# Now let's calculate the segment growth rates using the weighted methodology
def calculate_segment_growth_rates(source_growth_rates, segment_mappings, source_names):
    """Calculate weighted segment growth rates based on methodology"""
    
    segment_growth_rates = pd.DataFrame(index=source_growth_rates.index, columns=segment_names)
    
    for segment in segment_names:
        weights = segment_mappings[segment]
        
        for year in source_growth_rates.index:
            weighted_growth_rates = []
            total_weight = 0
            
            for i, source in enumerate(source_names):
                weight = weights[i]
                if pd.notna(weight) and weight > 0:  # Only consider non-zero weights
                    if source in source_growth_rates.columns:
                        growth_rate = source_growth_rates.loc[year, source]
                        if pd.notna(growth_rate):  # Only include if growth rate is available
                            weighted_growth_rates.append(growth_rate * weight)
                            total_weight += weight
                        else:
                            # If any required source has no growth rate, mark segment as N/A
                            weighted_growth_rates = []
                            break

def calculate_growth_rates(data):
    """Calculate year-over-year growth rates for each column"""
    growth_rates = pd.DataFrame(index=data.index[1:], columns=data.columns)
    
    for col in data.columns:
        for i in range(1, len(data)):
            current_val = data.iloc[i][col]
            previous_val = data.iloc[i-1][col]
            
            # Only calculate if both values are non-null and previous value is not zero
            if pd.notna(current_val) and pd.notna(previous_val) and previous_val != 0:
                growth_rate = ((current_val - previous_val) / previous_val) * 100
                growth_rates.loc[growth_rates.index[i-1], col] = growth_rate
            else:
